.TH "debug_register" 9 "debug_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
debug_register \- creates and initializes debug area with default file mode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "debug_info_t *" debug_register
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "int pages_per_area "  ","
.BI "int nr_areas "  ","
.BI "int buf_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
Name of debug log (e.g. used for debugfs entry)
.IP "pages_per_area" 12
Number of pages, which will be allocated per area
.IP "nr_areas" 12
Number of debug areas
.IP "buf_size" 12
Size of data area in each debug entry
.SH "RETURN"
- Handle for generated debug area
- NULL if register failed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates memory for a debug log.
The debugfs file mode access permissions are read and write for user.
Must not be called within an interrupt handler.
